'''Panno''' was a [[Dressellian/Legends|Dressellian]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] hailing from his [[Species/Legends|species']] [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[Dressel/Legends|Dressel]] who became a [[General/Legends|general]] and aided fellow Dressellian General [[Orrimaarko/Legends|Orrimaarko]] in leading the militant [[Dressellian resistance|resistance]] against the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] occupation of their native [[Planet/Legends|planet]]. He later joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and gained the [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] of [[Major/Legends|major]], serving as a [[Scout/Legends|scout]] and as a tactician who helped plan logistics for the Alliance's special operations and [[Commando/Legends|commando]] strikes. In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], Panno participated in the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] as part of the [[Endor strike team/Legends|strike team]] on the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]], which destroyed the [[Endor shield generator bunker|shield generator]] protecting the Imperial [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]].

==Biography==
===Dressellian resistance and Alliance service===
{{Quote|We have stolen a small Imperial shuttle. Disguised as a cargo ship and using a secret Imperial code, a strike team will land on the moon and deactivate the shield generator.|General Crix Madine, outlining the strike team's role in the Endor mission|audio=Madine-Imperialshuttlestolen.flac|<ref name="ROTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref>}}
Panno was a [[Dressellian/Legends|Dressellian]] [[Gender/Legends|male]]<ref name="CCG" /> who hailed from<ref name="HH" /> his<ref name="Hasbro" /> [[Species/Legends|species']] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Dressel/Legends|Dressel]]<ref name="HH" /> and became a [[General/Legends|general]] at some point<ref name="Stay on Target" /> during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], which was fought between the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="CCG" /> As a result of the Imperial occupation of their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]], fellow Dressellian General [[Orrimaarko/Legends|Orrimaarko]] led the species' militant [[Dressellian resistance|resistance]] against the Empire with the assistance of Generals Panno and [[Neeralli]].<ref name="Stay on Target" />

[[File:Holoprojector_-_Home_One.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Panno (left; the middle Dressellian) was present at a Rebel briefing for the Battle of Endor.]]
By [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="Galactic Files">{{Topps|set=2013 Topps Star Wars Galactic Files Series 2|cardname=#529 - Major Panno|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/93283/cid/6569555/2013-Topps-Star-Wars-Galactic-Files-Series-2-529-Major-Panno}}</ref> Panno, by then a former [[Commando/Legends|commando]], joined the Alliance,<ref name="CCG" /> to which he was followed by communications expert [[Olander Brit]].<ref name="Britcard">{{CCG|set=Death Star II Limited|cardname=Major Olander Brit}}</ref> Panno attained the [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] of [[Major/Legends|major]] within the Alliance, serving as a [[Scout/Legends|scout]] and tactician. In the latter role, Panno assisted Alliance General [[Crix Madine/Legends|Crix Madine]] with planning logistics for special operations<ref name="CCG" /> and commando strikes.<ref name="Hasbro" /> In that [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="Galactic Files" /> the Alliance learned that the Empire was constructing a [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]] over the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]], prompting them to organize an effort to [[Battle of Endor/Legends|destroy]] the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

Along with Orrimaarko, Panno was among the Alliance [[Trooper/Legends|troops]] who attended a briefing held aboard the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|Star Cruiser]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], which saw a [[Endor strike team/Legends|strike team]] organized to infiltrate Endor and destroy the Death Star's [[Endor shield generator bunker|shield generator]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]].<ref name="ROTJ" /> After aiding General Madine with plotting the strike team's destruction of the [[SLD-26 planetary shield generator/Legends|planetary shield generator]],<ref name="Hasbro" /> both Panno<ref name="Set Piece" /> and Orrimaarko<ref name="egtas">[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|''The Essential Guide to Alien Species'']]</ref> joined the assembled strike team.<ref name="ROTJ" />

===Infiltrating Endor===
{{Quote|Take the squad ahead. We'll meet at the shield generator at 0300.|General Han Solo, to Major Bren Derlin|audio=SoloDerlin.flac|<ref name="ROTJ" />}}
Panno<ref name="Set Piece" /> and the rest of the strike team infiltrated Endor aboard a stolen Imperial [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|shuttle]], the [[Tydirium/Legends|''Tydirium'']]. Posing as Imperials, they bypassed the [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] [[Blockade/Legends|blockade]] in Endor's [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]]. Once on Endor, the strike team proceeded to reconnoiter the area but soon encountered Imperial [[Scout trooper/Legends|scout trooper]] patrols,<ref name="ROTJ" /> forcing Alliance General [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] to direct the strike team's Major [[Bren Derlin/Legends|Bren Derlin]] to lead the [[Squad/Legends|squad]] ahead and rendezvous with him at the [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|shield generator]] bunker.<ref name="Night Attack">{{WEGCite|story=Night Attack|book=Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi}}</ref>

[[File:AT-ST_negvv.png|thumb|right|200px|Panno and the others in the strike team disabled an All Terrain Scout Transport (pictured).]]
Making their way toward the [[Deflector shield/Legends|shield]] generator later that [[Local day/Legends|afternoon]],<ref name="Night Attack" /> Panno<ref name="Set Piece" /> and the others in the strike team bypassed several Imperial scouts without compromising their position. At nightfall, they camped in a well-covered shallow [[Water/Legends|ravine]], posting two sentries and setting up a [[blanket grid]] with their [[Security scanner|scanning equipment]]. They were barely into their first [[Sleep/Legends|sleeping]] shift when an Imperial [[All Terrain Scout Transport/Legends|All Terrain Scout Transport]] [[Walker/Legends|walker]] moved toward their position.<ref name="Night Attack" />

When it was obvious the walker would not bypass them, the squad quickly [[Jammer/Legends|jammed]] the walker's transmissions and disabled its spotlights before circling around the machine to keep it blind as to the source of the attack. However, the AT-ST then opened fire at random, which greatly risked alerting other Imperials to the squad's presence. The group's [[Medic/Legends|medic]], [[Corporal/Legends|Corporal]] [[Delevar]], in turn fired a [[Smoke canister/Legends|smoke canister]] directly into one of the walker's [[Cockpit/Legends|cockpit]] [[Viewport/Legends|viewports]], forcing its [[Vehicle Command Crewer|pilots]] to abandon the vehicle and surrender to the strike team. After forcing the walker [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] to make a few call-ins to explain their vehicle's absence,<ref name="Night Attack" /> Panno<ref name="Set Piece" /> and the rest of the squad continued on the following morning and rendezvoused with Solo at the shield generator as planned.<ref name="Night Attack" />

===Alliance victory===
Meanwhile, Solo and the remainder of the strike team's command crew had formed an alliance with Endor's native [[Ewok/Legends|Ewoks]], who showed the Alliance a route to the shield bunker's rear entrance. Solo led the strike team into the bunker's interior, where they began placing explosive charges to destroy the shield generator before being ambushed by [[Tempest Force/Legends|Imperial forces]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

[[File:Ewok_village.jpg|thumb|left|300px|The celebration at Bright Tree Village, which Panno attended]]
Subsequently led back outside the bunker, the strike team's capture proved short-lived as the Ewoks aided the Alliance by counter-attacking the Imperials, culminating in the strike team ultimately retaking the bunker and successfully destroying the shield generator. With the shield generator's destruction, the Death Star was ultimately destroyed by the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] above Endor, leading to a major victory for the Alliance. Following the battle, Panno was among the many who later attended the victory celebrations in the Ewoks' [[Bright Tree Village/Legends|Bright Tree Village]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Personality and traits==
Panno had [[Color/Legends|light brown]] skin and yellow [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="CCG" /> He stood at 1.82 [[Meter/Legends|meters]] in height and weighed 80 [[Kilogram/Legends|kilograms]].<ref name="HH" />

==Skills and abilities==
Panno was a shrewd tactician, experienced in fighting against overwhelming enemy numbers.<ref name="HH" /> He earned high marks for his fighting and planning in various battles. With Panno serving as a commando, scout, or tactician based on when the situation called for it,<ref name="Galactic Files" /> his strike team service<ref name="Set Piece" /> constituted the first function.<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Equipment==
Panno wielded an impressive assortment of weapons against his opponents in various battles.<ref name="Galactic Files" /> He was individually armed with a [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]],<ref name="Hasbro" /> a [[Blaster rifle/Legends|blaster rifle]], a [[Vibroblade/Legends|vibroblade]], [[Stun grenade/Legends|stun grenades]], and [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonators]].<ref name="HH" /> He also wore a pair of [[Goggles/Legends|goggles]] and had a brown, hooded [[Cloak/Legends|cloak]] covering a [[Alliance military uniform/Legends|uniform]] that was similar in appearance to the [[Alliance Cold Weather armor]] sans [[Alliance Cold Weather Headgear|headgear]], gloves, and [[Alliance Cold Weather Backpack/Legends|backpack]]. Panno's uniform further differed from the Cold Weather [[Armor/Legends|armor]] through him wearing [[Forest/Legends|forest]] camouflage pants.<ref name="Hasbro" />

During the briefing on ''Home One'', Panno's uniform was overlaid with a white cloak rather than a brown one.<ref name="ROTJ" /> Along with all members of the Endor strike team, he was equipped with basic commando gear, which included a standard [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]], a low-feedback scanner, a [[Sensor scrambler (equipment)|sensor scrambler]], a [[Sound suppressor|heavily muffled]] [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]], and full forest-camouflage fatigues.<ref name="GG5">[[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi (Second Edition)|''Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi'', Second Edition]]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Panno_behind_the_scenes.png|thumb|right|300px|Panno standing behind the camera assistant during filming]]
Portrayed by an uncredited extra, Panno first appeared in the [[1983]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="ROTJ" /> The ''Home One'' scenes were filmed throughout the week of Tuesday, [[February 16]], [[1982]] at Stage 5 of [[Elstree Studios]],<ref name="BTS">{{WebCite|url=https://swnz.co.nz/2017/03/11/gerald-home-tessek-squid-head-mon-calamari-officer-2|text=Gerald Home as Tessek (Squid Head) and Mon Calamari Officer|author=G., Matt|date=2004-06-11|work=[https://swnz.co.nz Star Wars New Zealand]|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/JbkiZ}}</ref> while the film's later victory celebration scenes were filmed between [[January 20]] and [[January 22|22]] that year on Stage 3 in [[Wikipedia:Crescent City, California|Crescent City]], [[Wikipedia:California|California]].<ref name="making">''[[The Making of Return of the Jedi]]''</ref> The vests worn by Panno and the other Dressellians in the film were reused from the Alliance Cold Weather armor outfits seen in the earlier [[1980]] film [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']].<ref name="Set Piece" />

In [[2000]], [[Decipher]] would first name the character in their [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game's]] ''[[Death Star II Limited]]'' expansion set.<ref name="CCG" /> In [[2006]], [[Lucasfilm]] [[Holocron continuity database]] keeper [[Leland Chee]] theorized that Panno may be visible boarding the ''Tydirium''.<ref name="Chee blog">{{Blog|holocron|26|General Solo's Rebel strike team}}</ref> While no Dressellians are visible boarding the shuttle, there are some hooded figures that may include Panno.<ref name="ROTJ" />

